---  
description: Use when creating Sitecore React component files, registering components in .sitecore/component-map.ts, or validating naming across filename, componentName, and map key.  
globs: ["src/components/**/*.ts", "src/components/**/*.tsx", ".sitecore/component-map.ts"]  
alwaysApply: false  
---  
  
Component code rules:  
- Put components under `src/components/<category>/<component-name>.tsx`  
- Use kebab-case filenames  
- Export `Default` at minimum  
- Import Sitecore field helpers from `@sitecore-content-sdk/nextjs`  
- Extend your props from project `ComponentProps`  
- Use optional chaining  
  
Registration rules:  
- Register in `.sitecore/component-map.ts`  
- The map key must match the rendering `componentName` exactly  
- Example: `['article-cards', { ...articlecards, componentType: 'client' }]`  
  
Naming chain must align:  
- File: `article-cards.tsx`  
- Map key: `article-cards`  
- Rendering `componentName`: `article-cards`  
  
Operational note:  
- Restart the Next.js dev server after changing `.sitecore/component-map.ts`  